{"name": "py-moneyed", "metadata": {"name": "py-moneyed", "version": "3.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 6 - Mature", "Environment :: Other Environment", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Topic :: Office/Business :: Financial", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": "", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": "https://py-moneyed.readthedocs.io/en/latest/", "dependencies": ["babel", "typing-extensions"], "summary": "Provides Currency and Money classes for use in your Python code.", "upload_time": 1669584577}, "documentation": ["```{image} https://github.com/py-moneyed/py-moneyed/workflows/build/badge.svg\n:alt: Build Status\n:target: https://github.com/py-moneyed/py-moneyed/actions?query=workflow%3Abuild\n```\n\n```{image} https://badge.fury.io/py/py-moneyed.svg\n:alt: Latest PyPI version\n:target: https://pypi.org/project/py-moneyed/\n```\n\n```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/py-moneyed/badge/?version=latest\n:target: http://py-moneyed.readthedocs.io/en/latest/?badge=latest\n```\n\n# Overview\n\nThe need to represent instances of money frequently arises in software\ndevelopment, particularly any financial/economics software. To address that\nneed, the py-moneyed package provides the classes of Money and Currency, at a\nlevel more useful than just using Python's Decimal class, or (\\$DEITY forbid) the\nfloat primitive. The package is meant to be stand-alone and used directly, or\nbe subclassed further. py-moneyed is BSD-licensed.\n\n## Quick start\n\nTo install:\n\n```\npip install py-moneyed\n```\n\nUse:\n\n```python\nfrom moneyed import Money, USD\n\nfive_dollars = Money(5, USD)\n```\n\nYou then use `Money` objects as if they were numbers, and they behave\nsensibly. See [docs](https://py-moneyed.readthedocs.io/en/latest/) for more\ninformation (or the `docs/` folder).\n\n## History\n\nSome of the py-moneyed code was first derived from python-money\navailable via this URL: <http://code.google.com/p/python-money/>\nDue to inactivity, it was forked by @limist in 2010 and later\nmoved to the py-moneyed organization.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "moneyed.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "moneyed.utils.A", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "moneyed.utils.R", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "moneyed.utils.cached_property", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "moneyed.utils.cached_property.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "collections.abc.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "[A]", "xref": null, "params": null}, {"name": "R", "xref": {"fqname": "R", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "moneyed.utils.cached_property.__get__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "instance", "type": {"name": "A", "xref": {"fqname": "A", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "type", "type": {"name": "type", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "R", "xref": {"fqname": "R", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Decorator that creates conver